 /* 7. List of Products

You will receive an array of products. Print a numbered array of all the products ordered by name.
Example
Input Output
['Potatoes', 'Tomatoes', 'Onions', 'Apples'] 1.Apples 2.Onions 3.Potatoes 4.Tomatoes
['Watermelon', 'Banana', 'Apples'] 1.Apples'Potatoes', 'Tomatoes', 'Onions', 'Apples'] 2.Banana 3.Watermelon

Hints
· The sort function rearranges the array in ascending order
· Finally, we have to print our sorted array. To do that we loop through the array
· We use i + 1, because we want to start counting from 1  */


function arrOfProducts(products){

   products.sort();
   for (let i = 0; i < products.length; i++){
    products[i] = `${i+1}.${products[i] }`;
    console.log(products[i]);
   }
}

arrOfProducts(['Potatoes', 'Tomatoes', 'Onions', 'Apples']);
arrOfProducts(['Watermelon', 'Banana', 'Apples']);
